Executive Summary
On September 2, 2025, Desktop II triggered a Windows Security alert indicating suspicious PowerShell behavior consistent with fileless execution patterns.
Although no confirmed compromise was identified, the device underwent full incident-level remediation, including:
• Multi-stage malware remediation
• Full firewall reconstruction (inbound and outbound zero-trust model)
• PowerShell remoting disablement
• Protocol surface reduction
• BIOS firmware validation and update
• Router replacement and network hardening
• Credential security overhaul
The system now operates under a hardened security baseline with no indicators of compromise.

